@02: The update-rc.d command is a utility to modify startup scripts, whereas the init.d scripts are a collection of scripts to be run on command. I wouldn't recommend removing scripts from init.d, as they aren't running anyway until you tell them to.

@i2p over Tor: Yeah, I've done that. Laggy. As. Fuck. But pretty secure. I just don't give a shit, really, I'd rather dirty up VMs on an encrypted HOST and then trash them.

