Also, I'd like to add that, though I have recently been accused by several people of getting into hardware hacking, this is not the case. Sure, this is fun. Alright, I'm learning things, and I like soldering (mainly because I fancy it as a sort of 20th century alchemical operation). But, may I remind you, I am a <em>theoretical</em> physicist. I disdain physicality. I like theory. I know Common Lisp and use emacs. I research and train artificial intelligences. This hardware hacking is a means to the end of being able to better test those artificial intelligences. So don't you worry -- I'm not going to go around making goddamned LED pacman signs any time soon.

